The Croatian Assembly – one of the last remaining initiators – approved the new bill on Wednesday, without opposition. 51 deputies voted in favour and 35 voted against it. Depentalised abortion has been in effect in Croatia since March 1, 1978, reports Index.hr . The new bill will abolish some of the current restrictions connected with illegal abortion; however, the debate to legalize abortions up to the 12th week has failed in the Croatian Assembly in a split decision. 35 deputies voted in favour of the d

Today the abortion rate is lower in Croatia than it was in 1992, even as population has increased. These days people choose not to have abortions. According to the data from the Croatian Institute of Public Health, the abortion rate in 1992 was 61.6 percent per 1,000 women aged 15 to 44. In 1991, 50.436 abortions were registered in Croatia, compared to 20.740 in 2019 – a more than 59 percent drop over 28 years, according reports CIN .
